# Using shadcn-svelte Components

This project uses **shadcn-svelte** as the primary component library. Always prefer using existing shadcn-svelte components over creating custom components from scratch.

## Component Discovery Process

Before creating a new component:

1. **Check existing components** in `resources/js/lib/components/ui/`
2. **Search the shadcn-svelte documentation** at [https://www.shadcn-svelte.com/docs/components](https://www.shadcn-svelte.com/docs/components)
3. **If a component exists**, use it instead of building custom solutions
4. **If a component doesn't exist locally**, install it using the CLI

## Installing Components

To add a new shadcn-svelte component, use:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn-svelte@latest add <component-name>
```

Examples:
```bash
# Add a single component
pnpm dlx shadcn-svelte@latest add button

# Add multiple components
pnpm dlx shadcn-svelte@latest add card dialog form
```

